[1] Australia
Date: Wed, 23 Oct 2002 12:52:20 +1100
From: Paul Roche <Paul.Roche@health.gov.au>

Imported Cholera cases Australia
----------------------------
The National Notifiable Diseases Surveillance System (NNDSS) has recorded 3
recent cases of imported cholera in Australia. Details of the 3 cases are
as follows:
1 case of an infection with non-cholera Vibrio acquired in China (report
date 19 Jul 2002)
1 case _V. cholerae_ 01 Ogawa acquired in Pakistan (report date 21 Aug 2002)
1 case _V. cholerae_ 01 acquired overseas in Vietnam (report date 1 Oct 2002).
--
Dr Paul Roche
Epidemiologist
Department of Health and Ageing, Canberra
<Paul.Roche@health.gov.au>
